</div><a id="comment-9607"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/story-bsg-god-gog#comment-9607" class="active">God is a plot killer</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Quantum Iguana (not verified) on Tue, 2009-04-21 10:10.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>There's a reason deus ex machina is considered a bad thing, and it's not from any opposition to God. Invoking divine activity to resolve the story tends to render the actions of the human characters pointless. It renders the story "there exists a problem... blah, blah, blah... God fixes it", with the "blah, blah, blah" being all the human actions in the story.</p>
<p>Even in the 10 Commandments divine intervention is limited, allowing the actions of the human characters to do most of the driving of the story.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links"><li class="first last comment_reply"><a href="/comment/reply/914/9607" class="comment_reply">reply</a></li>
</ul></div>
